  Scenario: two table
    Given the following json:
    """
    [[{"name": "Tom", "age": 10}], [{"name": "John", "age": 15}]]
    """
    Then the following verification should pass:
    """
    :[
      >>| name  | 'Tom' |
        | age   | 10    |
      >>| name  | 'John' |
        | age   | 15     |
    ]
    """
    And the inspect should:
    """
    : [[0]: >>| name | : 'Tom' |
    | age | : 10 |, [1]: >>| name | : 'John' |
    | age | : 15 |]
    """
    Then the following verification should pass:
    """
    :[
      >>| name  | 'Tom' |
        | age   | 10    |

      >>| name  | 'John' |
        | age   | 15     |
    ]
    """
    And the inspect should:
    """
    : [[0]: >>| name | : 'Tom' |
    | age | : 10 |, [1]: >>| name | : 'John' |
    | age | : 15 |]
    """
    Then the following verification should pass:
    """
    :[  | >>    | 0     |
        | name  | 'Tom' |
        | age   | 10    |
        ,
        | >>    | 0     |
        | name  | 'John' |
        | age   | 15     |
    ]
    """
    And the inspect should:
    """
    : [[0]: | >> | 0 |
    | name | : 'Tom' |
    | age | : 10 |, [1]: | >> | 0 |
    | name | : 'John' |
    | age | : 15 |]
    """
    Then the following verification should pass:
    """
    :[  | >>    | 0     |
        | name  | 'Tom' |
        | age   | 10    |

        | >>    | 0     |
        | name  | 'John' |
        | age   | 15     |
    ]
    """
    And the inspect should:
    """
    : [[0]: | >> | 0 |
    | name | : 'Tom' |
    | age | : 10 |, [1]: | >> | 0 |
    | name | : 'John' |
    | age | : 15 |]
    """
    Then the following verification should pass:
    """
    :[  | >>    | 0     |
        | name  | 'Tom' |
        | age   | 10    |,
        | >>    | 0     |
        | name  | 'John' |
        | age   | 15     |
    ]
    """
    And the inspect should:
    """
    : [[0]: | >> | 0 |
    | name | : 'Tom' |
    | age | : 10 |, [1]: | >> | 0 |
    | name | : 'John' |
    | age | : 15 |]
    """

